CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 13, 1962, pg. 7 reads: "Luncheon Climaxes Week-Long Commemoration of Dr. Carver - Two distinguished national leaders challenged America to live up to its basic principles, when they addressed a capacity audience in attendance at the 18th Annual Carver Week Luncheon in Georgian Room of the Hotel Webster Hall, last Friday afternoon."
TitMainTitle: Man standing at podium at long head banquet table, with men and women seated on right side of him, and audience seated around banquet tables in foreground, in Webster Hall during Eighteenth Annual Carver Week luncheon
